title: Resistance Of Mrs Brown
description:
5 x 15 mins

London, 1942(ish). Britain is under Nazi rule. Mrs Brown is a middle class woman whose husband was killed at Dunkirk and has thus taken on the role of a tea lady working for the German army in London. She is approached by the British Resistance and asked to take on a role which could change the course of the war - but at what personal cost?
